00:49:00.560 --> 00:49:04.770 align:middle line:84%
you ignite that
power of possibility.

00:49:04.770 --> 00:49:07.700 align:middle line:84%
And especially when the
breathing becomes, also,

00:49:07.700 --> 00:49:10.310 align:middle line:84%
on the subconscious
level, so strong that it

00:49:10.310 --> 00:49:13.760 align:middle line:84%
leads your movements,
it leads your thoughts

00:49:13.760 --> 00:49:16.030 align:middle line:90%
in that direction.

00:49:16.030 --> 00:49:20.040 align:middle line:84%
>> So as kids, we are
normally in this deep state--

00:49:20.040 --> 00:49:22.260 align:middle line:84%
a dream state, this alpha
and the theta state.

00:49:22.260 --> 00:49:23.525 align:middle line:90%
We get into it really easy.

00:49:23.525 --> 00:49:25.650 align:middle line:84%
And then we unlearn that,
because our teacher says,

00:49:25.650 --> 00:49:28.290 align:middle line:90%
stop dreaming, stay focused.

00:49:28.290 --> 00:49:30.300 align:middle line:90%
So we lose that.

00:49:30.300 --> 00:49:33.180 align:middle line:10%
>> A lot of literature, culture,
art was created in dream

00:49:33.180 --> 00:49:34.030 align:middle line:10%
states.

00:49:34.030 --> 00:49:36.840 align:middle line:10%
So for example, Mary Shelley
came up with Frankenstein

00:49:36.840 --> 00:49:38.250 align:middle line:10%
in her dreams.

00:49:38.250 --> 00:49:41.790 align:middle line:84%
Paul McCartney came up with
"Yesterday" in his dream.

00:49:41.790 --> 00:49:45.630 align:middle line:84%
Elias Howe created the
sewing machine in his dream.

00:49:45.630 --> 00:49:49.560 align:middle line:10%
The periodic table came
to a chemist in his dream.

00:49:49.560 --> 00:49:51.888 align:middle line:84%
So many times, you'll
come up with answers,

00:49:51.888 --> 00:49:53.430 align:middle line:84%
you'll come up with
solutions, you'll

00:49:53.430 --> 00:49:56.132 align:middle line:84%
come up with inventions,
works of art, in your dreams.

00:49:56.132 --> 00:49:59.580 align:middle line:90%


00:49:59.580 --> 00:50:03.120 align:middle line:84%
>> Learning how to get back
into that dream state is the key

00:50:03.120 --> 00:50:05.858 align:middle line:84%
to being successful
in visualization.

00:50:05.858 --> 00:50:07.275 align:middle line:84%
So the first step
in visualization

00:50:07.275 --> 00:50:09.030 align:middle line:84%
is you want to know
how to relax yourself.

00:50:09.030 --> 00:50:14.522 align:middle line:84%
So you can breathe deep, do
just a simple meditation.

00:50:14.522 --> 00:50:16.855 align:middle line:84%
At a certain point, you're
going to feel really relaxed,

00:50:16.855 --> 00:50:18.800 align:middle line:84%
and you're not
fidgeting anymore.

00:50:18.800 --> 00:50:20.050 align:middle line:90%
Then you're in a deeper state.

00:50:20.050 --> 00:50:22.540 align:middle line:84%
Maybe you're not-- your
mind's not fidgeting either.

00:50:22.540 --> 00:50:24.100 align:middle line:84%
That's the time to
do visualization.

00:50:24.100 --> 00:50:26.660 align:middle line:84%
And when you do it
then, it just imprints.

00:50:26.660 --> 00:50:27.460 align:middle line:90%
You just get it.

00:50:27.460 --> 00:50:30.255 align:middle line:84%
So then you want to
imagine, or feel.

00:50:30.255 --> 00:50:32.380 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't necessarily--
you don't have to see it--

00:50:32.380 --> 00:50:34.463 align:middle line:84%
a lot of times when you
first learn visualization,

00:50:34.463 --> 00:50:35.915 align:middle line:90%
you can't see it.

00:50:35.915 --> 00:50:38.290 align:middle line:84%
It's a skill that you get
better and better at over time.

00:50:38.290 --> 00:50:39.320 align:middle line:90%
But you can feel it.

00:50:39.320 --> 00:50:42.250 align:middle line:84%
You can feel what it feels to
run faster than the other guy,

00:50:42.250 --> 00:50:45.910 align:middle line:84%
or to have the weight
melting off of your body,

00:50:45.910 --> 00:50:47.787 align:middle line:84%
or achieve whatever
athletic performance.

00:50:47.787 --> 00:50:49.120 align:middle line:90%
You can feel what it feels like.

00:50:49.120 --> 00:50:51.250 align:middle line:90%
You can hear the crowd shouting.

00:50:51.250 --> 00:50:54.040 align:middle line:84%
You can feel the wind on your
face as you're running by.

00:50:54.040 --> 00:50:56.080 align:middle line:84%
And you can imagine
different things.

00:50:56.080 --> 00:51:01.015 align:middle line:84%
When an athlete does
visualization, the muscles,

00:51:01.015 --> 00:51:03.760 align:middle line:84%
